OpenMorph
Geometric Field Intelligence
A deterministic geometric field framework built on two coprime primes — 13 and 11 — that
organizes any input geometrically and produces certified fingerprints.
No training. No labels. No domain configuration. No neural networks. No gradient descent.
No model weights.
The field is the program.
What Is OpenMorph?
OpenMorph is a new computing architecture. It processes any data through a 143-node
geometric field governed by eleven derived constants. Every input receives a deterministic
geometric fingerprint. Every computation is cryptographically certified. Every detection is
provable.
The same engine — without changing a single line of code — can detect cybersecurity
anomalies, classify proteins, identify financial fraud, separate dark matter signatures, or
monitor your device in real time.
It gets stronger the more data it processes. It gets stronger the more users connect to it.
Every user is a node. Every node feeds the collective field. The collective field feeds back to
every node.
