Quick Start — Kernel
from openmorph import Morph
m = Morph()
m.receive("anything")
m.step()
print(m.oav) # 11-dimensional fingerprint
print(m.signals) # 13 correction signals
print(m.distance) # distance from baseline
print(m.fingerprint) # 16-char hex ID
print(m.certificate) # SHA-256 certificate
print(m.merkle) # Merkle root of all certs
print(m.afq) # current breathing state
print(m.at_attractor()) # at equilibrium?
print(m.energy) # total field energy
print(m.abundance) # composite health metric
Spawn and Back-Propagate
child = m.spawn()
child.receive("child data")
child.step(10)
m.backpropagate(child)
Compare
a = Morph("A")
b = Morph("B")
a.receive("network traffic")
b.receive("login attempt")
a.step()
b.step()
print(Morph.compare(a, b))
Run Interactive
python openmorph.py
Type anything at the MORPH > prompt. See the field respond.
Quick Start — Companion
python openmorph_companion.py
That’s it. OpenMorph warms, starts monitoring your device, and begins pulsing
automatically. No interaction required.
It watches: clipboard, files, contacts, photos, reminders, motion sensors, system state,
network changes. Everything that happens on your device flows through the field.
Connect Users
You and another person on the same network:
python openmorph_companion.py peer=192.168.1.50
Replace with their IP address. They do the same with yours. Now both of your devices feed
the same collective field. The field feeds back to both of you.
Add more people. Every new node strengthens every other node.
The Eleven Constants
All derived from two prime numbers. None are configurable.
Constant Value What It Is
S 13 Segments (prime)
R 11 Radii (prime, coprime to S)
N 143 Nodes (S x R)
BUO 1 Base Unit of Organization
LEAN 0.01 Phase increment per cycle
ROT 0.03 Rotation increment per cycle
DECAY 0.97 Field activity decay
RESET 0.25 Quadrant boundary reset
WARM 629 Warmup cycles (ceil(2pi / LEAN))
SINGULARITY 0.1875 Invariant ratio (3/16)
OFFSET 1/13 Hangover modulus
How It Works
Warmup: 629 cycles. The field reaches attractor equilibrium [3, 3, 3, 4] by geometric
necessity.
Injection: Data enters as subjects. SHA-256 determines the node. BUO=1 added at that
node. Position is everything. Magnitude is irrelevant.
Forward pass: Couple neighboring nodes along the CRT traversal. All 143 nodes visited
exactly once.
Return pass: Local correction (neighbor delta) and global correction (AFQ geometry at
n%4). Back-propagation through the traversal.
AFQ breathing: 18 states. Integer partitions of 13 into 4 parts. The field breathes between
states based on field statistics. Maximum one transition per cycle.
Hangover: Non-Markovian memory. The field never forgets. Residual energy from prior
states carries forward indefinitely.
Signals: 13 correction signals from weighted radii sums plus SINGULARITY times the
predictive gradient. When a signal exceeds SINGULARITY (0.1875), the kernel spawns.
Spawning: Child inherits complete parent state. No depth limit. No width limit. Child
processes independently. Child back-propagates to parent. The field determines structure,
not the programmer.
Certificates: Every cycle, injection, and spawn produces a SHA-256 certificate chained to
all prior certificates. Merkle tree proves integrity across entire history. One bit changed
anywhere, ever, produces a different root. Tamper detection is total.
Architecture
Layer 1: Your adapter
Converts your domain objects to subject strings.
You build this. It's two functions.
Layer 2: OpenMorph Kernel
receive() -> step() -> oav -> signals -> certificate
Always identical. Domain-agnostic. Never modified.
Layer 3: Your interpreter
Reads OAV, signals, certificates in your domain terms.
You build this.
The kernel is the invariant. You build the adapters for whatever you want to do with it.
What Makes It Different
No training. Detection begins immediately from the first event.
No domain configuration. Same engine for any data type.
No model updates. Novel patterns detected by geometric deviation, not signature
matching.
Cryptographic proof. Every decision is mathematically verifiable.
Gets stronger with use. More data, more spawns, more hangover, stronger field.
Gets stronger with users. More nodes, stronger collective field.
Deterministic. Same inputs always produce same outputs.
Zero dependencies. Pure Python. Standard library only.
Use It For Whatever You Want
Cybersecurity. Fraud detection. Protein classification. Supply chain authentication.
Document integrity. Device monitoring. Anomaly detection. Research reproducibility.
Identity binding. Or something nobody has thought of yet.
The geometry doesn’t care what your data is. It organizes everything the same way. You
decide what the results mean.
